\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d thrown more mana at this foe than he\u8217\'92d even had for the first fight and still had a fair bit left in the tank if he needed it. Now if only he had more effective spells to use. His Explosive Mana Spikes were good when he could pierce the enemy and have them explode in the wound they left, but when they exploded on impact a good bit of the force was dispersed. Sadly, without a light source he could hardly study his theory primer and look for a method to improve them and he had no desire to attract the kind of attention a light might draw. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 As he recalled, ratels were mostly solitary and fiercely territorial by nature. Unless the System had changed that, he should be safe where he was for some time. Few predators willingly challenged honey badgers after all, and it would at least take some time for the local competition to work up the courage to test the badger\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s territory.  }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Marcus resumed his meditation position and spent several long minutes reviewing aspects of the Magical Theory that the System had forcibly loaded into his brain. As he understood it, if he could unlock his racial elemental affinity, he should be able to infuse that element into his bolts and barriers for additional effects. It was just a matter of identifying it and spending some time familiarizing himself with the feel of that sort of elemental mana. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 So he sank back into meditation, turning his focus inward and tried to submerge his senses into his Mana Core. It was a slow and deliberate process, but after some time, he managed it. He could feel the mana brushing along his projected consciousness, could feel the power in it and he focused on that feeling. His senses tingled with the power of the Mana, his nostrils filling with the acrid tang of corrosion and the slight burn of ozone. He studied his mana for a long time and was startled to discover two potent affinities within it. The stronger of the two was a powerful corrosive affinity, which suggested an acid spitting dragon of some sort. The nominally weaker affinity was a lightning affinity, only that didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t really make sense. He was supposed to have a single powerful elemental affinity from his race, wasn\u8217\'92t he.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 So he studied the mana even more closely, spending a few hours manipulating it and seeing how it responded. Which was how he discovered it wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t two separate affinities at all. It was a single affinity that combined aspects of the acid and lightning affinities to form some kind of caustic eldritch lightning, a lightning that burns, shocks and can even dissolve what it strikes. What the hell kind of dragon used that as a breath weapon? Apparently the kind his Dragonkin bloodline was descended from.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He exited his meditation and checked his pending System notifications to see what he could learn.<!$Scr_Ps::0>}
